comments:
Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).

On 1.4.1889 the part of the parish of Ashton under Lyne in the borough 
    of Stalybridge was transferred from Lancashire to Cheshire. In 1894 this area 
    became part of the parish of Stalybridge, so that thereafter Ashton under Lyne 
    was again wholly in Lancashire. See also Table 2, notes (a), (b) and (k).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Ashton under Lyne 
    in Audenshaw urban district. See also Table 2, note (k).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Droylsden in Manchester 
    County Borough. See also Table 2, note (e).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. Abolished 
    1.4.1914 and added to the parish of Lees.
See Table 2, note (a).
See Table 2, notes (a), (c), (d), (j) and (k).
See Table 2, notes (a) and (l).
See Table 2, notes (h) and (k).
See Table 2, notes (a) and (g).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Longdendale 
    and Hyde. See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Denton. See also 
    Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and added to the parish of Longdendale. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Ashton under Lyne 
    in Hurst urban district. See also Table 2, note (k).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed parts of the parishes 
    of Dukinfield, Hattersley and Matley. See also Table 2, note (l).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Ashton under Lyne 
    in Lees urban district. See also Table 2, note (l).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).
Created 1.4.1936 from the parishes of Mottram, Hollingworth, Hattersley and Matley. See also Table 2, note (l).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish 
    of Droylsden. See also Table 2, note (i).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Stalybridge, 
    Hyde, Dukinfield and Longdendale. See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 out of the parts of the parishes of Ashton under 
    Lyne, Saddleworth, Tintwistle and Stayley, in Mossley municipal borough. See 
    also Table 2, notes (f) and (k).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and added to the parish of Longdendale. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).
See Table 2, notes (a) and (g).

Created 1894 out of the parts of the parishes of Dukinfield, Stayley and Ashton under Lyne, in Stalybridge municipal borough. See also Table 2, note 
    (l).

On 1.4.1889 the part of the parish of Stayley in the borough of Mossley 
    became part of Lancashire. Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Stalybridge and Mossley. See also Table 2, note (a).

On 1.4.1889 the part of the parish of Tintwistle in the borough of 
    Mossley became part of Lancashire. In 1894 this area became part of the parish 
    of Mossley, so that thereafter Tintwistle was again wholly in Cheshire. See 
    also Table 2, notes (a) and (l).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Ashton under Lyne. See also 
    Table 2, note (k).

    Table 2, note (k).
